column5: Qualified open water diver :) :) :)
It was 4:20 when I took this picture. Hardest bloody hill to get up of the whole trip.
The kitchen has a particularly good view this evening

Final selfie with the river after 1723km. Finished in an town called Walwa. Tomorrow we start heading back past Wabba Wilderness Park towards Albury to get a train to Melbourne. Has been an awesome journey. I suggest you plan your next adventure now!
Views here are epic!
Hume bridge, nowhere to stop to take a selfie
So much water!!
1000 miles! And worked out so that I'm on top of the Hume Dam, pretty good view up here :)
Jen on the way through
More river crossings!
First fire I've ever made without a lighter. Such an amazing feeling when the spark finally takes and you see flames!
Crossing the border again
Yet another caravan park camp. Passed at least 20 bush camps on the river today, all underwater. Damn floods!
They like their giant things out here. First the cod, noe the strawberry!
Long unsealed roads today. Almost back with the Murray after a bit of a detour.
Nice forest track, hard camping round here as everywhere is flooded!
Awesome farm themed post boxes
I found a giant cod.
Back to nature for tonights camp but everything is a bit flooded. Hope this isn't a omen for things to come!
2 new tyres, new chain, lots of new tubes and a new helmet and ready to hit the road again :)
I've found what can only be described as a 5 star hotel. Has running water from a tap and heating! Time to wash and repair everything that is dirty / broken.
Hammock life
Some serious off road riding this morning. Got everything dry from the river crossing and now everything is covered in mud!
Ended up being so seep I had to swim! Only 5 more trips to make.
OMG. Wish me luck, this crossing is cray cray.
Tempting dirt jumps but better not with a full load.
Baked potato for dinner :)
View from my hammock. Just watched a bird fishing really close as it didn't notice me.
This evenings river side spot. Hammock rigging is interesting as each spot requires a slightly different solution. Pretty damn good view from my bedroom window :)
Hit the road jack, and don't come back no more no more no more no more. Hit jack, and don't you come back no more

Best beer in the world ever! After 110k of pretty relentless riding in strong winds and heat found a caravan park that will have me for the night and the owner gave me one of his beers. Bit better than puddle water!!!

So isolated here. Seen 3 trucks all day. Ran out of water but found a puddle so put the water filter & UV steripen to good use. 60k to Wentworth but have an awesome tailwind. Hope they have a massive ice cream shop!!
Morning tea
Camp this evening feels like I'm on an African savanna. Just saw a couple of kangeroos come right past my camp.
Not single a single other human all day yet today. Few kangaroos though :)
This photo doesn't even do justice to just quite how long this road is. There is nothing here apart from hundreds of flies and the odd dead lizard.

Leaving Renmark to head out towards Mildura now. Gets more remote now so phone signal may go and I'm getting very low on battery so may not be able to post as much or not at all for a few days. Don't worry, I'm OK!

Fire wood all prepared for this evening. Just found out that whilst there are not crocodiles in SA there are tiny little scorpions. Certainly makes collecting firewood more exiting not knowing what you'll find under every log!!
This feels like the most remote place I've been so far. There isn't even a road. Some of this terrain is interesting on a fully loaded tourer.
So quite here I have the whole ferry to myself. The weather feels a little foreboding.
Quite barren here
Mosquito nets are the new cool look this season
Cool camping spot this evening apart from the flies.
Pretty nice spot. Glad that last road is over. Went on for hours!
I wonder if this road ever ends?
Good spot for breakfast
Camp for tonight. Weather says its clear all night so going so go sans tarp and do some star gazing.
Fuck. Got to get my bike up there. Feels soo hot already. Definite example of type 2 fun.
Good as new. Thanks Phil, they are still going strong.
Oh no! I just bust me plugga.
My bike wanted its picture taken too
First ever time I've had crocodile! Tastes like a meaty fish. Mmmm.
Time for a swim?
Lots of nothing out here
Ferry crossing selfie
Home for the night
Pro tip: Use the sole of your flip flop as a plate
Can just see the Murray over the hills
Evening fire next to the Murray
